						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar built into the Peddāpuram gate in the Missionary's compound.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1139, Karkaṭa.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the gift of one Permāṇḍi-māḍa for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Sōmeśvara of Tilaśyāva-tīrtha by Nūṅkama, daughter of Kāmasāni. The maintenance of the lamp was entrusted to the mahājanas.</p>						

						</summary>
